radiographic_examinations.findings: The cerebral sulci, ventricles, and extra-axial CSF-containing spaces are mildly enlarged. The gray-white matter differentiation is well preserved. No acute ischemic infarct, intracranial hemorrhage or space-occupying lesion. Periventricular confluent low attenuation consistent with small vessel ischemic disease. Cystic lesion involving the pineal gland with peripheral calcification likely represents a simple cyst and is unchanged. Visualized paranasal sinuses and mastoid air cells are clear.
